[{'title': 'Boskalis Innovation Challenge - 2014', 'date': {'start': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2014}, 'end': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2014}}, 'description': 'The first edition of the Boskalis Innovation Challenge has been organized in 2014 and was a great success. Leading up to the event over 70 ideas have been submitted. On the day of the final event the seven most innovative ideas have been pitched in front of a jury and an audience, and at the end of the day the winners were selected. After the event, all of the seven ideas that were presented at the final event have been developed further with help of the Boskalis Research & Development Department.
 
In light of the success of the BIC 2014, it is decided to organize a new Boskalis Innovation Challenge in 2015. This year the goal will not only be to receive as much valuable and innovative ideas as possible. The aim is also to facilitate participation and interaction between as many colleagues as possible in developing the different ideas leading up to the final event. 

', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Niels', 'last_name': 'Asjee', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Project Manager - Scarborough Export Trunkline Seabed Intervention and Shore Crossing Project'}]}, {'title': 'Boskalis Ichthys GEP Project - NINA - Reward & Recognition Program 2013 - 2015', 'date': {'start': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2013}, 'end': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2013}}, 'description': 'Boskalis Ichthys GEP Project - NINA - Reward & Recognition Program 2013 - 2015

To continue to promote our No Incidents No Accidents safety culture, the NINA Reward & Recognition Program originally developed and implemented on the Gorgon Project was introduced on both the Ichthys LNG Onshore Project and Ichthys GEP Project in Darwin – Northern Territory – Australia as of January 2013. 

The NINA Reward & Recognition Program was developed to identify and promote qualities and/or behaviors in line with our NINA spirit, being:

1.	Innovation and Improvement;
2.	Demonstrated Leadership; and 
3.	High Standards and Continued Excellence. 

These identified qualities were used to develop the criteria for the NINA Reward & Recognition Program. 

Everyone involved in the Project is encouraged to nominate an individual, a team or workgroup for recognition. 
Nominations are emailed to the program co-coordinator or handed in to worksite Supervisor using a Nomination Form prior to the last day of each month. 

The awards are announced on a monthly basis, with the winner(s) choosing one of the following rewards: 

- Donation to nominated charity; and / or
- Reward of own choice. 

Once nominations close, the judging panel meet to discuss the nominees, casting one vote each. 

Since the program’s inception on the Ichthys Projects winners have successfully varied by persons, workgroups and criteria.

The contract awarded by Woodside Energy Ltd. (Woodside), in its capacity as operator of the Scarborough Joint Venture, potentially carries a value of EUR 145 million if all options are called and is subject to a final investment decision which is expected in 2020. The preparatory activities for this multidisciplinary project have commenced recently. The seabed intervention and shore crossing works are scheduled to start in March 2021 with an expected completion mid-2022. The scope of activities includes the pre-trenching of the nearshore pipeline route along a 50 kilometers section, offshore deep water excavation works, pre-lay and post-lay rock installation for pipeline and fiber optic cable crossings, the post installation burial and other protection works to ensure the stability of the pipeline. Support for the shore crossing to the onshore processing facility on the Burrup Peninsula as well as rock supply are also part of the contract. Boskalis will work to make best use of local content, based on capability and competitiveness, for the delivery of its scope of work. 

Boskalis will deploy a wide variety of its in-house specialist expertise and equipment including a trailing suction hopper dredger, a backhoe dredger, a dynamically positioned fallpipe vessel and rock installation vessel, survey vessels and an offshore construction vessel. 

The Scarborough gas field is situated approximately 375 kilometers offshore the Burrup Peninsula in North West Australia. The proposed export pipeline will transport natural gas between the Scarborough Floating Production Unit and the onshore processing plant.
